ds/2025/02/Morrissey-performing-3.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Morrissey-performing-3-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Morrissey-performing-3-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Morrissey-performing-3-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Morrissey-performing-3-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Morrissey-performing-3-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3841183" class="wp-caption-text">莫里西（Morrissey）在2015年6月19日在特拉华州多佛（Dover）的萤火虫音乐节（Firefly Music Festival）的第2天演出。 （照片由ILYA S. SAVENOK/Getty Images for Firefly）</figcaption></figure><p>他的7月9日演出<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-cancels-sold-out-nottingham-show-3467003">将在诺丁汉的皇家音乐厅举行</a>- 随后被取消，主持演出的场所以“不可预见的情况”为主持。</p><p>在<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-announces-december-2024-shows-including-new-years-eve-gig-in-la-3819363">短暂的洛杉矶演出到2024年</a>，以及<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-announces-2024-north-american-tour-kicking-off-on-halloween-3781107">10月下旬和11月的北美巡回演出</a>之后，所有新节目都将在洛杉矶演出中进行。</p><p>现场表演遵循歌手最近几个月对新材料的新更新 - 即长期延迟的专辑《少年篝火》。</p><p>这位歌手继续在<a href="https://www.morrisseycentral.com/messagesfrommorrissey/387636-bonfire-of-teenagers-is-none-of-your-business">其网站</a>上分享有关“篝火”状态的声明，指责国会大厦的记录“法西斯主义”，并具有“审查的文化”。他还说，他<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-is-quickly-coming-around-to-that-belief-that-capitol-is-sabotaging-his-new-album-3394087">“迅速来到了”信念，即该品牌只签署了&#39;青少年&#39;&#39;&#39;&#39;为了破坏它的篝火</a>。 </p><figure id="attachment_3841184" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3841184" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3841184" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Morrissey-posing.jpg" alt="莫里西（Morrissey）于2014年11月29日在英国伦敦举行的02竞技场上现场直播。 （吉姆·戴森（Jim Dyson）/电线图）" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Morrissey-posing.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Morrissey-posing-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Morrissey-posing-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Morrissey-posing-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Morrissey-posing-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/Morrissey-posing-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3841184" class="wp-caption-text">莫里西（Morrissey）于2014年11月29日在英国伦敦举行的02竞技场上现场表演。 （吉姆·戴森（Jim Dyson）/电线图）</figcaption></figure><p> He also took it a step further and <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-claims-capitol-records-boss-wants-to-wreck-his-career-3516249">alleged that the CEO of Capitol Records was trying to derail his career</a> , before then taking to his website to say he was <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-says-hes-been-gagged-over-release-of-bonfire-of-the-teenagers-we-are-still-in-the-grip-of-idiot-culture-3792060">being “gagged” over the release of &#39;Bonfire Of The Teenagers&#39;</a> .</p><p> Issues with the album continued into 2024, with Morrissey <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-says-hes-bought-back-the-rights-to-two-albums-from-capitol-records-3714862">buying back the rights to two of his albums</a> in April of that year following a long-running dispute with Capitol Records. He described the situation to fans as “a long, hard, bloody war.”</p><p> Last November, he told a crowd at one of his shows in the US that he was <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-says-war-on-free-speech-is-stopping-him-releasing-music-3814002">being prevented from releasing new music due to a war on “free speech”</a> , saying: “You cannot speak freely in England. If you don&#39;t believe me, go there. Express an opinion, you&#39;ll be sent to prison. It&#39;s very, very difficult.”</p><p> The post <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/morrissey-hits-out-at-trolls-whose-heads-are-not-attached-to-their-bodies-for-claiming-upcoming-show-has-been-cancelled-3841163">Morrissey hits out at “trolls whose heads are not attached to their bodies” for claiming upcoming show has been cancelled</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
